Of such adventurers , the most fortunate was the emperor Leo the Third , who , from the mountains of Isauria , ascended the throne of the East . 
The sect of the Iconoclasts was supported by the zeal and despotism of six emperors , and the East and West were involved in a noisy conflict of one hundred and twenty years . 
In their loud and loyal acclamations , they celebrated the merits of their temporal redeemer and to his zeal and justice they intrusted the execution of their spiritual censures . 
Our original , but not impartial , monuments of the Iconoclasts must be drawn from the Acts of the Councils , tom . 
and the historical writings of Theophanes , Nicephorus , Manasses , Cedrenus , Zonoras , c . 
