On a less conspicuous theatre it had been used , in the vith and viith centuries , by the provincial bishops of Britain and Spain . 
The royal unction of Constantinople was borrowed from the Latins in the last age of the empire . 
Constantine Manasses mentions that of Charlemagne as a foreign , Jewish , incomprehensible ceremony . 
