Childeric was deposed jussu , the Carlovingians were established auctoritate , Pontificis Romani . 
, pretend that these strong words are susceptible of a very soft interpretation . 
Be it so yet Eginhard understood the world , the court , and the Latin language . 
Since the revolt of Italy and the loss of the Exarchate , the distress of the Romans had exacted some sacrifice of their independence . 
The Roman ambassadors presented these patricians with the keys of the shrine of St . 
Peter , as a pledge and symbol of sovereignty with a holy banner which it was their right and duty to unfurl in the defence of the church and city . 
The power and policy of Charlemagne annihilated an enemy , and imposed a master . 
At the distance of one mile , the Flaminian way was lined with the schools , or national communities , of Greeks , Lombards , Saxons , c . 
the Roman youth were under arms and the children of a more tender age , with palms and olive branches in their hands , chanted the praises of their great deliverer . 
Nor was the Frank content with these vain and empty demonstrations of respect . 
The people swore allegiance to his person and family in his name money was coined , and justice was administered and the election of the popes was examined and confirmed by his authority . 
Except an original and self inherent claim of sovereignty , there was not any prerogative remaining , which the title of emperor could add to the patrician of Rome . 
Of these the Franciscan Pagi is the most disposed to make the patrician a lieutenant of the church , rather than of the empire . 
seems to allow of no palliation or escape . 
The gratitude of the Carlovingians was adequate to these obligations , and their names are consecrated , as the saviors and benefactors of the Roman church . 
In this transaction , the ambition and avarice of the popes have been severely condemned . 
Perhaps the humility of a Christian priest should have rejected an earthly kingdom , which it was not easy for him to govern without renouncing the virtues of his profession . 
But in the rigid interpretation of the laws , every one may accept , without injury , whatever his benefactor can bestow without injustice . 
The Greek emperor had abdicated , or forfeited , his right to the Exarchate and the sword of Astolphus was broken by the stronger sword of the Carlovingian . 
Peter , and completed , by this voluntary surrender , the present circle of the ecclesiastical state . 
But , in the cooler moments of absence and reflection , he viewed , with an eye of jealousy and envy , the recent greatness of his ecclesiastical ally . 
weighs this donation with fair and deliberate prudence . 
and the Codex Carolinus supposes , this ample gift . 
Both are contemporary records and the latter is the more authentic , since it has been preserved , not in the Papal , but the Imperial , library . 
