After pursuing above six hundred years the fleeting Caesars of Constantinople and Germany , I now descend , in the reign of Heraclius , on the eastern borders of the Greek monarchy . 
Their collections , versions , and histories , I shall occasionally notice . 
In the vacant space between Persia , Syria , Egypt , and Aethiopia , the Arabian peninsula may be conceived as a triangle of spacious but irregular dimensions . 
From the northern point of Beles on the Euphrates , a line of fifteen hundred miles is terminated by the Straits of Bebelmandel and the land of frankincense . 
About half this length may be allowed for the middle breadth , from east to west , from Bassora to Suez , from the Persian Gulf to the Red Sea . 
The sides of the triangle are gradually enlarged , and the southern basis presents a front of a thousand miles to the Indian Ocean . 
The common benefits of water are an object of desire and contest and such is the scarcity of wood , that some art is requisite to preserve and propagate the element of fire . 
Such is the general and genuine picture of the climate of Arabia . 
The experience of evil enhances the value of any local or partial enjoyments . 
The maritime districts of Bahrein and Oman are opposite to the realm of Persia . 
The geographers of Arabia may be divided into three classes . 
