Before he spoke , the orator engaged on his side the affections of a public or private audience . 
His memory was capacious and retentive his wit easy and social his imagination sublime his judgment clear , rapid , and decisive . 
Yet the book of nature and of man was open to his view and some fancy has been indulged in the political and philosophical observations which are ascribed to the Arabian traveller . 
