The mysteries of the Trinity and Incarnation appear to contradict the principle of the divine unity . 
The creed of Mahomet is free from suspicion or ambiguity and the Koran is a glorious testimony to the unity of God . 
These sublime truths , thus announced in the language of the prophet , are firmly held by his disciples , and defined with metaphysical precision by the interpreters of the Koran . 
A philosophic theist might subscribe the popular creed of the Mahometans a creed too sublime , perhaps , for our present faculties . 
