Disdaining the penance and merit of a hermit , he observed , without effort or vanity , the abstemious diet of an Arab and a soldier . 
On solemn occasions he feasted his companions with rustic and hospitable plenty but in his domestic life , many weeks would elapse without a tire being kindled on the hearth of the prophet . 
The heat of the climate inflames the blood of the Arabs and their libidinous complexion has been noticed by the writers of antiquity . 
