Many learned men have doubted the existence of a communication by water between the Red Sea and the Mediterranean by the Nile . 
Yet the fact is positively asserted by the ancients . 
speaks of it in the most distinct manner as existing in his time . 
says that he went by water from Alexandria to Clysma , on the Red Sea . 
Testimonies of the th and of the th century show that the communication was not interrupted at that time . 
