Some enemies yet remained for the sword of Musa . 
They were successively besieged and reduced by the labor of Musa , who transported his camp from the Boetis to the Anas , from the Guadalquivir to the Guadiana . 
The constancy of the besieged was at length subdued by famine and despair and the prudent victor disguised his impatience under the names of clemency and esteem . 
