When the Arabs first issued from the desert , they must have been surprised at the ease and rapidity of their own success . 
Forty six years after the flight of Mahomet from Mecca , his disciples appeared in arms under the walls of Constantinople . 
The Arabian fleet cast anchor , and the troops were disembarked near the palace of Hebdomon , seven miles from the city . 
But the besiegers had formed an insufficient estimate of the strength and resources of Constantinople . 
