This defect , if it really existed , must have stimulated the ingenuity of the Arabs to invent or borrow . 
our ciphers are not of Indian or Arabic invention . 
They were used by the Greek and Latin arithmeticians long before the age of Boethius . 
After the extinction of science in the West , they were adopted by the Arabic versions from the original Mss. , and restored to the Latins about the xith century . 
Note Compare , on the Introduction of the Arabic numerals , Hallam's Introduction to the Literature of Europe , p . 
