The emperor Theophilus , son of Michael the Stammerer , was one of the most active and high spirited princes who reigned at Constantinople during the middle age . 
In offensive or defensive war , he marched in person five times against the Saracens , formidable in his attack , esteemed by the enemy in his losses and defeats . 
These solicitations determined the emperor to wound his pride in so sensible a part . 
Sozopetra was levelled with the ground , the Syrian prisoners were marked or mutilated with ignominious cruelty , and a thousand female captives were forced away from the adjacent territory . 
In the revenge of his injury , the caliph prepared to retaliate a similar affront . 
The name of Amorium was inscribed on the shields of the Saracens and their three armies were again united under the walls of the devoted city . 
It had been proposed by the wisest counsellors , to evacuate Amorium , to remove the inhabitants , and to abandon the empty structures to the vain resentment of the Barbarians . 
The emperor embraced the more generous resolution of defending , in a siege and battle , the country of his ancestors . 
The Arabs were broken , but it was by the swords of thirty thousand Persians , who had obtained service and settlement in the Byzantine empire . 
They breathed at Dorylaeum , at the distance of three days and Theophilus , reviewing his trembling squadrons , forgave the common flight both of the prince and people . 
They had nearly been the witnesses of his shame . 
