In the first of these works he minutely describes the pompous ceremonies of the church and palace of Constantinople , according to his own practice , and that of his predecessors . 
In the second , he attempts an accurate survey of the provinces , the themes , as they were then denominated , both of Europe and Asia . 
In the fourth , of the administration of the empire , he reveals the secrets of the Byzantine policy , in friendly or hostile intercourse with the nations of the earth . 
