The emperor alone could assume the purple or red buskins , and the close diadem or tiara , which imitated the fashion of the Persian kings . 
Instead of red , the buskins of the Sebastocrator and Caesar were green and on their open coronets or crowns , the precious gems were more sparingly distributed . 
Beside and below the Caesar the fancy of Alexius created the Panhypersebastos and the Protosebastos , whose sound and signification will satisfy a Grecian ear . 
