The command of the Mediterranean , from the mouth of the Tanais to the columns of Hercules , was always claimed , and often possessed , by the successors of Constantine . 
Since the time of the Peloponnesian and Punic wars , the sphere of action had not been enlarged and the science of naval architecture appears to have declined . 
The language of signals , so clear and copious in the naval grammar of the moderns , was imperfectly expressed by the various positions and colors of a commanding flag . 
