But the Lombard princes of Benevento , Salerno , and Capua , were reluctantly torn from the communion of the Latin world , and too often violated their oaths of servitude and tribute . 
On that day the scale of war was turned against the Franks by the valor of the Saracens . 
A series of rebellions might dart a ray of truth into the palace of Constantinople and the illusions of flattery were dispelled by the easy and rapid success of the Norman adventurers . 
Your master , says Nicephorus , has given aid and protection prinminibus Capuano et Beneventano , servis meis , quos oppugnare dispono . 
