The zeal or gratitude of Gregory had promised to his valor the kingdoms of Greece and Asia his troops were assembled in arms , flushed with success , and eager for action . 
Their services were liberally paid by the license or monopoly of trade , a profitable gift of many shops and houses in the port of Constantinople , and a tribute to St . 
Mark , the more acceptable , as it was the produce of a tax on their rivals at Amalphi . 
