The revolution which transferred the sceptre from the Abbassides to the Fatimites was a benefit , rather than an injury , to the Holy Land . 
A sovereign resident in Egypt was more sensible of the importance of Christian trade and the emirs of Palestine were less remote from the justice and power of the throne . 
In the sea voyage of Palestine , the dangers were frequent , and the opportunities rare but the conversion of Hungary opened a safe communication between Germany and Greece . 
Stephen , the apostle of his kingdom , relieved and conducted his itinerant brethren and from Belgrade to Antioch , they traversed fifteen hundred miles of a Christian empire . 
After visiting the holy places , they embarked for Italy , but only a remnant of two thousand arrived in safety in their native land . 
