The conquest of Asia was undertaken and achieved by Alexander , with thirty five thousand Macedonians and Greeks and his best hope was in the strength and discipline of his phalanx of infantry . 
The value of these soldiers deserved a strict and authentic account and the flower of European chivalry might furnish , in a first effort , this formidable body of heavy horse . 
