The coolest scepticism will remember , that of these religious volunteers great numbers never beheld Constantinople and Nice . 
Yet the myriads that survived , that marched , that pressed forwards on the holy pilgrimage , were a subject of astonishment to themselves and to the Greeks . 
Their motives , their characters , and their arms , have been already displayed . 
A small remnant of the pilgrims , who passed the Bosphorus , was permitted to visit the holy sepulchre . 
Their northern constitution was scorched by the rays , and infected by the vapors , of a Syrian sun . 
In the dire necessity of famine , they sometimes roasted and devoured the flesh of their infant or adult captives . 
